%N A397922 Array read by antidiagonals: T(n,k) is the number of nonnegative integer matrices with a total of n rows and columns with each row sum and column sum nonzero and at most k, up to permutations of rows and columns, n >= 0, k >= 0.
%C A397922 Equivalently, T(n,k) is the number of bicolored multigraphs on n unlabeled vertices with no isolated vertices and vertex degrees at most k. The color classes are not interchangeable and edges may not connect vertices of the same color. Parallel edges are allowed, but not loops.
